0131\\u015f \\\"\\u015eir, Cadug\\u0259r v\\u0259 Qarderob\\\"dur. Lakin Lyuis bununla da dayanmad\\u0131. Sonra daha alt\\u0131 kitab \\u00e7\\u0131xd\\u0131 v\\u0259 onlar birlikd\\u0259 Narniya Salnam\\u0259l\\u0259ri kimi tan\\u0131nd\\u0131lar.Son \\u0259lli il \\u0259rzind\\u0259 \\\"Narniya Salnam\\u0259l\\u0259ri\\\" fantastik janr\\u0131n\\u0131 a\\u015faraq klassik \\u0259d\\u0259biyyat\\u0131n kanonunun bir hiss\\u0259sin\\u0259 \\u00e7evrildi. Yeddi kitab\\u0131n h\\u0259r biri \\u015fedevrdir, oxucunu sehrin reall\\u0131qla qovu\\u015fdu\\u011fu diyara c\\u0259lb edir v\\u0259 n\\u0259tic\\u0259d\\u0259 \\u0259hat\\u0259 dair\\u0259si n\\u0259sill\\u0259ri valeh ed\\u0259n uydurma d\\u00fcnyad\\u0131r.Bu n\\u0259\\u015fr yeddi kitab\\u0131n ham\\u0131s\\u0131n\\u0131 - q\\u0131sald\\u0131lmadan - bir t\\u0259sirli cildd\\u0259 t\\u0259qdim edir. Kitablar burada xronoloji ard\\u0131c\\u0131ll\\u0131qla t\\u0259qdim olunur, h\\u0259r bir f\\u0259sil orijinal r\\u0259ssam Pauline Baynes t\\u0259r\\u0259find\\u0259n ill\\u00fcstrasiya il\\u0259 b\\u0259z\\u0259dilib. Aldad\\u0131c\\u0131 d\\u0259r\\u0259c\\u0259d\\u0259 sad\\u0259 v\\u0259 birba\\u015fa \\\"The Chronicles of Narnia\\\" ilk n\\u0259\\u015fr olunduqdan \\u0259lli il sonra bel\\u0259, h\\u0259r ya\\u015fdan olan oxuculara dan\\u0131\\u015fan s\\u0259rg\\u00fcz\\u0259\\u015ftl\\u0259ri, personajlar\\u0131 v\\u0259 h\\u0259qiq\\u0259tl\\u0259ri il\\u0259 p\\u0259r\\u0259sti\\u015fkarlar\\u0131n\\u0131 ovsunlama\\u011fa davam edir.\",\"en\":\"Journeys to the end of the world, fantastic creatures, and epic battles between good and evil\\u2014what more could any reader ask for in one book? The book that has it all is The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe, written in 1949 by Clive Staples Lewis. But Lewis did not stop there. Six more books followed, and together they became known as The Chronicles of Narnia.For the past fifty years, The Chronicles of Narnia have transcended the fantasy genre to becom