a\\u0430\\u0445 \\u041d\\u0435\\u0432\\u0435\\u0440\\u043b\\u0435\\u043d\\u0434\\u0430\\u00bb \\u0438 \\u00ab\\u041d\\u0435\\u0437\\u043d\\u0430\\u043a\\u043e\\u043c\\u0435\\u0446, \\u0447\\u0435\\u043c \\u0444\\u0430\\u043d\\u0442\\u0430\\u0441\\u0442\\u0438\\u043a\\u0430\\u00bb).\",\"az\":\"Tam r\\u0259ngli 120-d\\u0259n \\u00e7ox foto\\u015f\\u0259kil v\\u0259 tam ssenari il\\u0259, rejissor Mark Forsterin sevimli bestseller roman\\u0131 \\u0259sas\\u0131nda filmin \\u00e7\\u0259kili\\u015finin arxas\\u0131ndak\\u0131 hekay\\u0259 (Canavar\\u0131n topu, He\\u00e7 yerd\\u0259 tap\\u0131lmayan \\u00f6lk\\u0259 v\\u0259 fantastikadan q\\u0259rib\\u0259).\"}', '{\"en\":\"With more than 120 photos in full color and the complete screenplay, the story behind the making of the movie based on the beloved bestselling novel directed by Marc Forster ( Monster\'s Ball, Finding Neverland , and Stranger Than Fiction ).\\r\\n\\r\\nBased on one of the most acclaimed novels in recent memory, The Kite Runner is a profoundly emotional tale of friendship, family, devastating mistakes, and redeeming love. In a divided country on the verge of war, two childhood friends, Amirand Hassan, are about to be torn apart forever. One boy\'s fearful act of betrayal will mark their lives forever and set in motion an epic quest for redemption. Now, after 20 years of living in America, Amir returns to a perilous Afghanistan under the Taliban\'s iron-fisted rule to face the secrets that still haunt him and take one last daring chance to set things right. This universal human story speaks to anyone who has every yearned for a second chance to make a change and find forgiveness.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis beautifully designed pictorial book includes the complete screenplay, highlighted by exquisite color photographs, behind-the-scenes stories about the production, the locations (the western Chinese desert that borders Afghanistan), the casting of the globally diverse cast and crew, and commentaries by novelist K